{# goal: Compute normalized convergence metric [0,1] for the essentialist 3-gate audit. metric = (gates_failed / 3) * 0.60 + (items_not_removed / total_items) * 0.40. weight: 0.60 for gate failures, weight: 0.40 for unresolved items. Emit reg.skill span (P9). UserPod_host mandatory (P12). #}
{# Computes normalized metric [0, 1] where 0 = fully converged (all gates pass, all items resolved) #}

INPUT: gates_failed = {{ gates_failed | default(0) }} (number of essentialist gates that failed: 0-3)
INPUT: gates_passed = {{ gates_passed | default(0) }} (number of gates that passed: 0-3)
INPUT: items_removed = {{ items_removed | default(0) }} (items deleted/merged/inlined by the essentialist)
INPUT: total_items = {{ total_items | default(0) }} (total items evaluated)
INPUT: items_not_removed = {{ items_not_removed | default(0) }} (items that survived all 3 gates)
INPUT: previous_metric = {{ previous_metric | default(1.0) }}
INPUT: userpod_host = {{ userpod_host }} (P12)

COMPUTE METRIC (weighted — evidence-based only, P8, P5):
- Gate failures weight: 0.60
  Score = (gates_failed / 3) * 0.60.
  0 gates failed = +0.00; 1 failed = +0.20; 2 failed = +0.40; 3 failed = +0.60.
  Each gate (Exist, Surface, Contract) carries equal weight within this dimension.
- Unresolved items weight: 0.40
  Score = (items_not_removed / max(1, total_items)) * 0.40.
  All items removed = +0.00; no items removed = +0.40; partial = proportional.

SUM = sum of contributions, clamp [0, 1].

CONVERGENCE CHECK (P9 — homeostatic regulation):
- Metric ≤ 0.10: near converged (all gates pass, most items resolved).
- Metric ≤ 0.10 AND relative improvement ≥ 5% from previous_metric: converged.
- If metric > 0.10 OR improvement < 5%: not converged — identify blockers.
- Blockers = specific gate failures (which gate: Exist/Surface/Contract),
  unresolved items (which items survived all 3 gates and why).

Regulation SPAN (P9):
- `reg.skill` is registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES` (`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`).
  Emit span unconditionally:
  (`target: "reg.skill"`, message: `"Regulation"`, operation: `"essentialist_convergence_check"`,
  metric, previous_metric, improvement_pct, blockers: [...], userpod_host, latency_ms).

OUTPUT FORMAT (JSON):
`{convergence_metric, previous_metric, improvement_pct, converged: bool,
blockers: [...], gates_failed, gates_passed, items_removed, total_items,
items_not_removed, userpod_host, reg_span_emitted: true}`.

5W1H GATE (P5 — minimal): Who = userpod host; What = convergence metric;
Where = essentialist audit cycle; When = after 3-gate evaluation; Why = P9
observable self-correction / P7 evolutionary progress; How = compute metric
+ check improvement + emit Regulation span + identify blockers.
All 6 present.

